docs.abstract: Following an Oakland tavern and its staff — from the tattooed bartender to the undocumented cleaner — as they weather the economic and emotional fallout of the coronavirus.
docs.snippet: Following an Oakland tavern and its staff — from the tattooed bartender to the undocumented cleaner — as they weather the economic and emotional fallout of the coronavirus.
docs.lead_paragraph: OAKLAND, Calif. — Cold beer flowed, soul music played and regulars lined the redwood bar to order tequila shots and tater tots. No one wore masks, many hugged, and the staff passed a joint out front.

headline.main: One Bar. Twelve Weeks. Seventeen Lives in Lockdown.
headline.print_headline: One Bar. 12 Weeks. 17 Lives In Flux.

docs.abstract: Tired of searching for good movies to stream and looking for something off the beaten path? We did the work for you.
docs.snippet: Tired of searching for good movies to stream and looking for something off the beaten path? We did the work for you.
docs.lead_paragraph: Weeks have stretched into months, and many of us are still spending a lot of our time inside, staring down an ever-shrinking queue of must-see movies. So it’s time to take some chances again, going beyond streaming platforms’ carefully curated front-page recommendations to check out less obvious choices: gnarly genre films, riveting documentaries, indie dramas and more of what’s hiding in the back rooms of your subscription services.

headline.main: 10 Streaming Movies to Take a Chance On
headline.print_headline: Here to Help; Four Streaming Movies to Take a Chance On
